            <scopecontent id="aspace_a2488798d85331e70cfa5c9477b31861">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>Series I consists of Arndt's collection of primary sources used for his research on Count Leon and his involvement in nineteenth-century German-American religious sects. Material includes documentation of the organization and leadership of the Harmony society, the New Philadelphia Congregation, and Germantown, Louisiana, printed material by and about Harmonists and Leonites, correspondence to and from sect members, photographs of residents of Germantown, Louisiana, maps used when the Leonites journeyed from Pennsylvania to Louisiana, and books from Johann Georg Goentgen's library.</p>
               <p>Document numbers in parentheses reflect Arndt's identification of the material. Material is also identified by number in a detailed list of collection contents filed in Box 1.</p>
            </scopecontent>
